For numerous optical properties of NaNbO3 and NaTaO3, the determination of dielectric function is instructive. How the electromagnetic waves propagate when the medium for them is changed and the interaction between phonons and electrons are described by the complex dielectric function. Given by Eq. (8),8εω=ε1ω+iε2ω,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
